01:11:25.960 --> 01:11:29.140
that alluded to the fact that
race is not a definitive line,

01:11:29.140 --> 01:11:30.040
right?

01:11:30.040 --> 01:11:32.890
You know, I always tell people
that the Irish and the Polish

01:11:32.890 --> 01:11:34.540
and the Italians,
they were not white

01:11:34.540 --> 01:11:35.540
when they came to this country.

01:11:35.540 --> 01:11:37.914
They were not-- they were
considered like a fundamentally

01:11:37.914 --> 01:11:38.584
different--

01:11:38.584 --> 01:11:40.000
of a fundamentally
different race.

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:43.630
And it was only over time
that they became white,

01:11:43.630 --> 01:11:45.490
that they were acculturated
and assimilated

01:11:45.490 --> 01:11:46.990
into whiteness in
the way that we

01:11:46.990 --> 01:11:50.420
think about it in a
specifically American context.

01:11:50.420 --> 01:11:52.630
And so we have all these stats.

01:11:52.630 --> 01:11:55.870
What is it, by 2043 or
something like that,

01:11:55.870 --> 01:11:59.900
that it's going to be a
majority minority country.

01:11:59.900 --> 01:12:03.010
Yes, and I think it's
important to consider

01:12:03.010 --> 01:12:05.560
the ways that certain people
who may not necessarily

01:12:05.560 --> 01:12:06.820
be considered--

01:12:06.820 --> 01:12:09.970
who are considered brown
now, or may not necessarily

01:12:09.970 --> 01:12:11.800
be considered such
30 years from now.

01:12:11.800 --> 01:12:14.065
I think all you have
to do is look at--

01:12:14.065 --> 01:12:17.380
think about if Ted Cruz didn't
have the last name Cruz,

01:12:17.380 --> 01:12:18.770
you know, what--

01:12:18.770 --> 01:12:23.020
there's nothing about his
politics that reflects brown--

01:12:23.020 --> 01:12:24.850
not to say brownness
and blackness

01:12:24.850 --> 01:12:27.370
is homogeneous in terms
of political talk.

01:12:27.370 --> 01:12:30.700
But you know, you
have Marco Rubio

01:12:30.700 --> 01:12:32.530
and you have Ted
Cruz as examples

01:12:32.530 --> 01:12:35.740
of people who but
for their last name,

01:12:35.740 --> 01:12:38.260
they would navigate the
world as white men, right?

01:12:38.260 --> 01:12:42.100
And I think Latino folks are--

01:12:42.100 --> 01:12:43.960
that is the next sort of--

01:12:43.960 --> 01:12:49.270
you have many people coming
to the United States who

01:12:49.270 --> 01:12:56.230
are of Latino origin
who marry white people,

01:12:56.230 --> 01:13:01.570
and their children might
not necessarily identify--

01:13:01.570 --> 01:13:03.910
depending-- and part of it
depends on their last name,

01:13:03.910 --> 01:13:05.159
it depends on a lot of things.

01:13:05.159 --> 01:13:07.390
But they might not
necessarily readily

01:13:07.390 --> 01:13:11.926
identify as a brown
person more than they

01:13:11.926 --> 01:13:13.050
would do as a white person.

01:13:13.050 --> 01:13:15.754
I think you see that
already beginning to happen.

01:13:15.754 --> 01:13:17.920
And I think that's going
to continue to happen and I

01:13:17.920 --> 01:13:20.336
wouldn't be surprised-- and
that's why I think people were

01:13:20.336 --> 01:13:21.453
kind of surprised at--

01:13:25.195 --> 01:13:28.090
at the exit polls from
the 2016 election,

01:13:28.090 --> 01:13:32.680
people were like, oh, like the
Latinx community is going to--

01:13:32.680 --> 01:13:35.980
like, that is who's going to
overwhelmingly vote Democrat

01:13:35.980 --> 01:13:37.190
and going to save everything.

01:13:37.190 --> 01:13:43.570
And I think it's 35% of
people who are on the census

01:13:43.570 --> 01:13:46.450
Hispanic voted for Trump.

01:13:46.450 --> 01:13:49.140
So like, it is, again,
these political blocs

01:13:49.140 --> 01:13:50.450
are not homogeneous.

01:13:50.450 --> 01:13:52.950
You have a lot of
people who think

01:13:52.950 --> 01:13:54.990
of themselves as
Hispanic, but also think

01:13:54.990 --> 01:13:57.060
of themselves as white.

01:13:57.060 --> 01:14:02.104
And over time, that is going
to continue to look different.

01:14:02.104 --> 01:14:04.020
The demographics of this
country are certainly

01:14:04.020 --> 01:14:06.930
shifting in ways that
are important and helpful

01:14:06.930 --> 01:14:08.940
for progressive politics.

01:14:08.940 --> 01:14:13.140
I think you also have a party
on the right who knows that,

01:14:13.140 --> 01:14:16.350
and that is why they try very
hard to suppress the vote,

01:14:16.350 --> 01:14:20.550
to gerrymander districts, and
to make it so that there's only

01:14:20.550 --> 01:14:23.619
a certain type of political
power in certain communities.

